notes: Pitfall||Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33|||http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Bait|Odontomachus, Pheidole and other myrmicinae. Video taken: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=awYW03666xM|7mEPE|Waypoint 190||2.5 hrs walk up (6:40 - 9:10). Some misting rain and wind but turned clear and dry in the pm. Traps down at 9:30-9:45. Put out almost 2/3rds of a roll of flagging tape on ascent. 2 videos taken. First at Bait 6 was of Odontomachs, Pheidole, Pentatomidae and a worm, and 2nd video was 2 small myrmicinae drinking. Page 130 in the book. 360 GigaPan at 6 (top) should see Odontomachus nest and the Trap 6.|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66877/|http://bit.ly/ebIlSI|http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|
sequencing_centers: Biodiversity Institute of Ontario|Biodiversity Institute of Ontario

notes: Pitfall||Set up Connor for the day working on Cacao 1999 malaise traps (2 in the day). Switching rental vehicles at 3pm. Completely clear, somewhat breezy and ciccadas calling all day. Very hot (>30 C). Traps out and bait down at 9:20am. GigaPan at Bait 6 was problematic (batteries died and the shutter arm fell off). took about 4hrs to finish with a hard re-start. Ticks everywhere. Videos of Atta at Bait 2, Large Camponotus at Bait 5, Crematogaster, Atta and Solenopsis at Bait 3 and Small Camponotus at Bait 4. All up at 2:50pm. Dominant species, Paratrechina and Solenopsis|Waypoint 33|||http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71622/|http://bit.ly/dQDt90|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Pitfall||7mEPE|Waypoint 190||2.5 hrs walk up (6:40 - 9:10). Some misting rain and wind but turned clear and dry in the pm. Traps down at 9:30-9:45. Put out almost 2/3rds of a roll of flagging tape on ascent. 2 videos taken. First at Bait 6 was of Odontomachs, Pheidole, Pentatomidae and a worm, and 2nd video was 2 small myrmicinae drinking.
